---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-options', text: 'Coverage Options for Couples', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Plan Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'joint-vs-individual', text: 'Joint vs Individual Plans', level: 2 },
  { id: 'special-considerations', text: 'Special Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Family Insurance', href: '/best/family-insurance' },
  { title: 'Maternity Insurance', href: '/best/maternity-insurance' },
  { title: 'Senior Insurance', href: '/best/senior-insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'coupleDiscount', header: 'Couple Discount' },
  { key: 'jointPolicy', header: 'Joint Policy' },
  { key: 'maternity', header: 'Maternity Add-On' },
  { key: 'flexibility', header: 'Plan Flexibility' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', coupleDiscount: '5-10%', jointPolicy: 'Yes', maternity: 'Optional', flexibility: 'Modular' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', coupleDiscount: 'Some plans', jointPolicy: 'Yes', maternity: 'Optional', flexibility: 'High' },
  { provider: 'Aetna International', coupleDiscount: 'Varies', jointPolicy: 'Yes', maternity: 'Optional', flexibility: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', coupleDiscount: 'Some plans', jointPolicy: 'Yes', maternity: 'Optional', flexibility: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', coupleDiscount: 'Per-person', jointPolicy: 'No', maternity: 'No', flexibility: 'Limited' },
];

const optionsColumns = [
  { key: 'option', header: 'Option' },
  { key: 'pros', header: 'Pros' },
  { key: 'cons', header: 'Cons' },
];

const optionsRows = [
  { option: 'Joint policy', pros: 'Simpler admin, shared deductible option, potential discounts', cons: 'Less flexibility, tied together' },
  { option: 'Individual policies (same insurer)', pros: 'Customize each plan, independent coverage', cons: 'Two separate policies to manage' },
  { option: 'Individual policies (different insurers)', pros: 'Best plan for each person\'s needs', cons: 'Most admin, no discounts' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Expat Insurance for Couples 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for expat couples. Find plans with couple discounts, joint policies, and flexible coverage options for partners living abroad."
  headline="Best Expat Insurance for Couples"
  subheadline="Moving abroad as a couple? Here are the best international health insurance options with couple discounts, joint policies, and flexible coverage for partners."
  heroImage="/images/answers/best-couple-insurance.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  showHeroCta={false}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Plans"
  ctaButtonHref="/compare/"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Top Picks for Couples</h2>
  <p>
    These insurers offer the best options for expat couples:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💑</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best for Couples</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-700 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Modular plans with couple discounts, joint policies, and flexible coverage options.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">👫</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best Premium Option</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Joint policies with excellent coverage and family-friendly pricing structure.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">🇺🇸</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Best with US Coverage</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Good joint policy options with strong US network for American couples.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="text-4xl mb-3">💡</div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Key Benefit</h3>
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-700 mb-2">Simplified Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Joint policies mean one renewal, one policy to manage, and often lower combined costs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-options">Coverage Options for Couples</h2>
  <p>
    Couples have several options for structuring their international health insurance:
  </p>

  <h3>Joint Policy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Both partners on single policy</li>
    <li>One premium, one renewal date</li>
    <li>Often eligible for couple discounts</li>
    <li>Can share family deductible</li>
    <li>Simpler administration</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Separate Individual Policies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Each partner has own policy</li>
    <li>Can customize each plan differently</li>
    <li>Independence if relationship changes</li>
    <li>Can use different insurers if needed</li>
    <li>More administrative work</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Considerations for Unmarried Partners</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Most insurers accept domestic partners</li>
    <li>Definition varies by insurer</li>
    <li>May need to share address</li>
    <li>Some require cohabitation period</li>
    <li>Verify eligibility before applying</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Coverage for Two"
    description="Compare plans with couple-friendly options."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Couple Coverage Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global — Best for Couples</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers excellent options for expat couples.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Joint policies available</li>
    <li>5-10% couple/family discounts</li>
    <li>Modular plans for customization</li>
    <li>Optional maternity coverage</li>
    <li>Partners can have different coverage levels</li>
    <li>Easy to add children later</li>
    <li>Single renewal and administration</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Premium pricing. Best value on mid-tier plans. Good flexibility for different needs within couple.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our full Cigna Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Bupa Global — Best Premium Option</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers comprehensive coverage for couples.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Joint policies with good discounts</li>
    <li>Excellent coverage options</li>
    <li>Optional maternity benefits</li>
    <li>Flexible plan structures</li>
    <li>Strong global network</li>
    <li>Premium service quality</li>
    <li>Easy family expansion</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Most expensive option. Best for couples wanting premium coverage. Worth it for comprehensive protection.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our full Bupa Global review</a></p>

  <h3>Aetna International — Best with US Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International works well for American couples abroad.
  </p>
  <p><strong>What works well:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Joint policies available</li>
    <li>Strong US network</li>
    <li>Good international coverage</li>
    <li>Familiar to US expats</li>
    <li>Maternity options</li>
    <li>Good for couples returning to US</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Considerations:</strong> Best for US-connected couples. Pricing competitive for US coverage. Good all-around option.</p>
  <p><a href="/providers/aetna-international">Read our full Aetna International review</a></p>

  <h2 id="joint-vs-individual">Joint vs Individual Plans</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={optionsColumns} rows={optionsRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>When to Choose Joint Policy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Married or long-term committed relationship</li>
    <li>Similar healthcare needs</li>
    <li>Want simplified administration</li>
    <li>Planning to stay together long-term</li>
    <li>Want potential discounts</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>When to Choose Separate Policies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Very different healthcare needs</li>
    <li>One partner needs specific coverage other doesn't</li>
    <li>Relationship situation uncertain</li>
    <li>Different citizenship/residency affecting options</li>
    <li>Employer covers one partner</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Shared vs Individual Deductibles</h3>
  <p>
    Options for deductible structure:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Individual deductible:</strong> Each person has own deductible</li>
    <li><strong>Family/shared deductible:</strong> Both contribute to one pool</li>
    <li>Shared can save money if one person has high costs</li>
    <li>Individual is fairer if needs are very different</li>
    <li>Not all insurers offer both options</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Find Your Perfect Match"
    description="Compare couple insurance options."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/compare/"
  />

  <h2 id="special-considerations">Special Considerations for Couples</h2>

  <h3>Planning for Family</h3>
  <p>
    If children are in your future:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Add maternity coverage now (waiting periods apply)</li>
    <li>Check how adding children affects premium</li>
    <li>Verify pediatric coverage quality</li>
    <li>Understand family policy pricing</li>
    <li>Plan ahead—maternity waiting periods are 10-12 months</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Age Differences</h3>
  <p>
    When partners are different ages:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Premiums usually based on each person's age</li>
    <li>Significant age gap means different costs</li>
    <li>Consider separate policies if big age difference</li>
    <li>Joint may not save money with age spread</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Different Health Needs</h3>
  <p>
    When one partner needs more coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Modular plans let you customize each</li>
    <li>One can have maternity, other not</li>
    <li>Different deductibles possible</li>
    <li>Separate policies may make more sense</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Relocation Flexibility</h3>
  <p>
    If your plans might change:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Verify coverage in potential destinations</li>
    <li>Check ease of address changes</li>
    <li>Understand what happens if one partner moves</li>
    <li>Global plans offer most flexibility</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Domestic Partners</h3>
  <p>
    Coverage for unmarried couples:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most major insurers accept domestic partners</li>
    <li>May need to cohabit or share address</li>
    <li>Some have time requirements (6-12 months together)</li>
    <li>Legal civil partnerships usually accepted</li>
    <li>Verify specific insurer requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do we have to be married for a joint policy?</h3>
  <p>
    No. Most international health insurers accept domestic partners, civil unions, and long-term cohabiting couples. Requirements vary—some need shared address, others require minimum time together. Verify with your chosen insurer.
  </p>

  <h3>Is a joint policy cheaper than two individual policies?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually yes. Many insurers offer 5-10% discounts for couple or family policies. Even without explicit discounts, administrative costs are lower. However, if needs differ significantly, individual policies might be more efficient.
  </p>

  <h3>Can we have different coverage levels on a joint policy?</h3>
  <p>
    With some insurers, yes. Modular plans (like Cigna Global) allow different modules for each person. Others require same coverage for both. Check specific insurer flexibility before deciding.
  </p>

  <h3>What happens if we separate?</h3>
  <p>
    Joint policy would need to be split into two individual policies. This may require new underwriting and could affect coverage for pre-existing conditions. Consider this risk when choosing joint vs individual policies.
  </p>

  <h3>Should we add maternity coverage now?</h3>
  <p>
    If children are possible within 2-3 years, add it now. Maternity has 10-12 month waiting periods. You can't add it after becoming pregnant. It's cheaper to remove later than to miss the window.
  </p>

  <h3>Can one partner be primary policyholder?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. On joint policies, one person is typically designated as the primary policyholder for administration purposes. Both partners have equal coverage rights. This doesn't affect coverage—just who receives communications.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This content is for informational purposes only. Couple coverage options vary by plan and insurer. We are not insurance brokers. Always verify current options directly with insurers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
